OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,F5p and 10p pieces ` identical in value
OL,7,Fand size to 1/- and 2/- pieces ` were
OL,8,Fin circulation from 1968. The following
OL,9,Fyear 50p pieces came into use. And a
OL,10,Fpound, of course , was still a pound.
OL,12,FIn practice, the only big overnight
OL,13,Fchange in 1971 concerned any price, or
OL,14,Ffraction of a price, of less than 2.5p
OL,15,F` old sixpences (value 2.5p) remained
OL,16,Flegal tender until 1980.
OL,18,FThere was advice on how to use up old
OL,19,Fcopper coins in the weeks afterwards.
OL,20,FOverpay and get your change in decimal
OL,21,Fcurrency.
