OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FAnd yet, this change was still a
OL,7,Fworrying and anxious time for a
OL,8,Fminority. Great efforts were made to
OL,9,Ftry to make it easier for them.
OL,11,FAnother big change in the 70s also
OL,12,Fprovoked concern for the vulnerable.
OL,14,FFor many people, the radio changes of
OL,15,F1978 simply meant retuning. Naturally
OL,16,Fthere was also a lot of promotion to
OL,17,Fhighlight the new station frequencies.
OL,18,FBut, again, for a minority this was a
OL,19,Fdifficult situation. Boy Scouts were
OL,20,Ftrained to help people retune.
