OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FSo, traditionally in Britain we have
OL,7,Foften gone to great lengths to help
OL,8,Fthose who are vulnerable for one reason
OL,9,For another with changes that were
OL,10,Fstraightforward for most of us.
OL,12,FThat is still true.
OL,14,FI bet few would notice the end of
OL,15,Fmedium wave radio.
OL,17,FRadio Ulster and many English local
OL,18,Fstations are already off MW.
