OL,3,GOPINIONCFreeview switch-off: a history
OL,4,Clesson
OL,5,
OL,6,FI would suggest it can be considered
OL,7,Fwhen Freeview accounts for less than
OL,8,F10pc of viewing.
OL,10,FThen a medium-term timetable along with
OL,11,Fpractical measures to help the
OL,12,Fvulnerable can be set out.
OL,14,FTalking about a TV switch off just now
OL,15,F` when it is a long time in the future
OL,16,F` may simply worry or scare some
OL,17,Fpeople.
OL,19,FAnd politicians should know there are
OL,20,Fsimply no votes in turning off TV.
